* has_many relationship with spouse (to access #spouses)
* #married which can be called on #spouses to find out if the marriage is current
* Marriage table
  * "Married" boolean column in Marriage table
  * "husband_id" and "wife_id" in Marriage table
  * Unique enforcement
* #marry which finds all instances of husband and wife and checks #married, then creates new marriage record and saves both.
* #divorce makes "Married" column false in both parties
* #die makes "Married" column false in both parties and "Living" column in Person table false for only that Person.